1
00:00:12,533 --> 00:00:13,867
<i> What happened here?</i>

2
00:00:14,400 --> 00:00:15,767
<i>- What did you do?
- Boss, wait...</i>

3
00:00:17,133 --> 00:00:18,167
<i> Reign, wait a minute.</i>

4
00:00:18,400 --> 00:00:19,367
<i> Hello, Sir Tonyo?</i>

5
00:00:19,500 --> 00:00:20,200
<i> Hello, Enriquez?</i>

6
00:00:20,333 --> 00:00:22,200
<i> Markus was killed last night.</i>

7
00:00:22,333 --> 00:00:23,233
<i> What?</i>

8
00:00:23,367 --> 00:00:24,300
<i> What is she doing here?</i>

9
00:00:24,433 --> 00:00:25,000
<i> Miss?</i>

10
00:00:25,133 --> 00:00:25,533
<i> Miss...</i>

11
00:00:25,667 --> 00:00:26,400
<i> Wake up, Miss.</i>

12
00:00:26,533 --> 00:00:27,367
<i> Help!</i>

13
00:00:27,500 --> 00:00:28,333
<i> Help!</i>

14
00:00:28,467 --> 00:00:29,433
<i> I'm very sorry,</i>

15
00:00:29,567 --> 00:00:32,333
<i>but the area where the woman
was found</i>

16
00:00:32,467 --> 00:00:33,700
<i>is a blind spot
in our CCTV coverage.</i>

17
00:00:33,867 --> 00:00:34,933
<i> There's an ATM here.</i>

18
00:00:35,067 --> 00:00:37,400
<i> Don't ATMs have built-in CCTV?</i>

19
00:00:37,533 --> 00:00:38,967
<i>We need to get a copy
from the bank.</i>

20
00:00:39,100 --> 00:00:41,733
<i>Enriquez, what time was Shaira
seen outside again?</i>

21
00:00:41,867 --> 00:00:43,600
<i>About four in the morning, Sir.</i>

22
00:00:43,733 --> 00:00:45,567
<i>There, you can see the car's
license plate number.</i>

23
00:00:45,700 --> 00:00:48,267
<i>Call your contact.
We need to find this car.</i>

24
00:00:48,400 --> 00:00:48,700
<i> Yes, Sir.</i>

25
00:00:48,867 --> 00:00:50,000
<i> Good day.</i>

26
00:00:50,133 --> 00:00:52,933
<i>I was just going to ask
if the car outside is yours.</i>

27
00:00:53,067 --> 00:00:54,367
<i> The car outside?</i>

28
00:00:54,500 --> 00:00:55,400
<i> He did run away!</i>

29
00:00:55,533 --> 00:00:57,667
<i>Sir, we didn't want that
to happen!</i>

30
00:00:57,800 --> 00:00:58,967
<i> We didn't know</i>

31
00:00:59,100 --> 00:01:00,933
<i>that the drugs would have
that effect on Shaira, Sir.</i>

32
00:01:01,067 --> 00:01:02,933
<i>What you did to Shaira
was no joke.</i>

33
00:01:03,067 --> 00:01:04,667
<i>You abandoned her
until she died.</i>

34
00:01:04,800 --> 00:01:06,167
<i>So if you really regret
what you did to Shaira,</i>

35
00:01:06,300 --> 00:01:07,767
<i>now is the time to make amends.</i>

36
00:01:07,933 --> 00:01:08,800
<i> Yes, yes, Sir.</i>

37
00:01:08,933 --> 00:01:11,200
<i>Okay, I'll cooperate with you,
Sir.</i>

38
00:02:09,467 --> 00:02:11,067
Doc Cecilia...

39
00:02:11,700 --> 00:02:12,467
coffee?

40
00:02:13,367 --> 00:02:14,067
Eric.

41
00:02:14,633 --> 00:02:15,500
Thank you.

42
00:02:16,367 --> 00:02:17,600
What are you doing here?

43
00:02:19,100 --> 00:02:21,800
I'm just following up
on the case,

44
00:02:21,933 --> 00:02:24,300
the one about Jane Doe.

45
00:02:24,433 --> 00:02:27,933
I thought Lieutenant Conde
would be handling this case?

46
00:02:29,200 --> 00:02:33,233
That's what I like about Conde,
he supports my love life.

47
00:02:34,267 --> 00:02:37,267
Anyway, what's the update?

48
00:02:38,667 --> 00:02:40,067
Here, check the pictures.

49
00:02:43,267 --> 00:02:45,833
Shaira Reyes, 19 years old,
female.

50
00:02:45,967 --> 00:02:49,700
I don't see any signs of blunt
force trauma or lacerations

51
00:02:49,867 --> 00:02:51,333
on any part of her body.

52
00:02:53,200 --> 00:02:54,100
Beautiful.

53
00:02:56,700 --> 00:02:57,567
What's beautiful?

54
00:02:59,800 --> 00:03:01,200
Isn't she dead already?

55
00:03:01,933 --> 00:03:02,700
Not her...

56
00:03:03,833 --> 00:03:04,567
you.

57
00:03:06,933 --> 00:03:09,067
Eric, didn't you say
you wouldn't bug me

58
00:03:09,200 --> 00:03:10,300
while I'm working?

59
00:03:11,567 --> 00:03:14,833
No. Okay, fine. I'm sorry.
Let's continue.

60
00:03:14,967 --> 00:03:17,400
Okay, what's the update
on Shaira?

61
00:03:18,133 --> 00:03:22,800
I don't see any signs of
scratches or aberrations,

62
00:03:22,967 --> 00:03:25,800
except for the bruises
around her wrists and ankles.

63
00:03:26,533 --> 00:03:28,433
But I was wondering...

64
00:03:29,500 --> 00:03:32,233
a pimple patch was found
on her face,

65
00:03:32,367 --> 00:03:33,933
even though she doesn't have
any pimples.

66
00:03:34,900 --> 00:03:37,133
What you discovered is great.

67
00:03:37,367 --> 00:03:39,333
Do you want us
to talk about it later?

68
00:03:39,467 --> 00:03:40,567
Let's have dinner together.

69
00:03:41,933 --> 00:03:43,333
You're really annoying, Eric.

70
00:03:43,733 --> 00:03:44,867
I'm not available later.

71
00:03:45,000 --> 00:03:45,967
I have a dinner date
with someone else.

72
00:03:46,100 --> 00:03:46,833
I'm sorry.

73
00:03:51,600 --> 00:03:52,667
She has a dinner date?

74
00:03:53,600 --> 00:03:55,367
Who is she having dinner with?

75
00:04:10,500 --> 00:04:13,167
Sir, chief is calling.
I'll just answer this.

76
00:04:14,000 --> 00:04:14,900
Hello, Chief?

77
00:04:20,467 --> 00:04:21,333
Really?

78
00:04:23,867 --> 00:04:26,300
Okay, Sir. Okay. Thank you.

79
00:04:28,300 --> 00:04:29,167
Sir.

80
00:04:29,300 --> 00:04:31,033
What's the news?
Why did chief suddenly call?

81
00:04:31,167 --> 00:04:33,367
Mayor Guerrero called him.

82
00:04:33,500 --> 00:04:35,267
He said he wants to form
a special task force

83
00:04:35,400 --> 00:04:36,367
here in Calabari.

84
00:04:36,500 --> 00:04:38,633
And he wants the two of us
to lead it.

85
00:04:40,533 --> 00:04:42,267
Congratulations, Enriquez.

86
00:04:42,700 --> 00:04:44,167
You deserve it.

87
00:04:45,667 --> 00:04:47,767
I just don't know
if my grandmother will agree

88
00:04:47,900 --> 00:04:50,300
because she doesn't like
Mayor Guerrero.

89
00:04:53,300 --> 00:04:55,400
Well, what will you do
if she doesn't agree?

90
00:04:58,867 --> 00:04:59,667
I don't know.

91
00:05:00,900 --> 00:05:01,967
I don't know yet.

92
00:05:04,133 --> 00:05:05,267
Hey, you!

93
00:05:05,933 --> 00:05:08,033
You two! Stop that!

94
00:05:08,367 --> 00:05:09,833
You're still young,
and you're such a flirt.

95
00:05:32,033 --> 00:05:32,900
- Sir...
- Yes?

96
00:05:33,633 --> 00:05:35,067
Just play along, Sir.

97
00:05:40,933 --> 00:05:41,533
Sir...

98
00:05:42,000 --> 00:05:43,800
we'd better just go back.

99
00:05:43,933 --> 00:05:45,000
It looks like
they won't let us in,

100
00:05:45,133 --> 00:05:46,967
let's just prepare well for it.

101
00:05:47,100 --> 00:05:48,700
It's risky, we might get caught.

102
00:05:50,100 --> 00:05:51,367
Come on. Let's go, Sir.

103
00:05:56,067 --> 00:05:57,167
Okay.

104
00:05:58,267 --> 00:05:59,800
No, just stay there.

105
00:05:59,933 --> 00:06:01,733
Go ahead, I'll follow.
Go! Go ahead!

106
00:06:02,200 --> 00:06:03,733
That's an order!
Go ahead, go up there!

107
00:06:28,200 --> 00:06:29,100
Cecilia...

108
00:06:30,300 --> 00:06:30,933
what's wrong?

109
00:06:34,633 --> 00:06:35,767
Nothing, Glen.

110
00:06:37,133 --> 00:06:38,067
I'm okay.

111
00:06:40,333 --> 00:06:41,533
Cecilia, please...

112
00:06:41,933 --> 00:06:43,633
we only see each other
once in a while,

113
00:06:44,100 --> 00:06:45,167
and you're acting like that.

114
00:06:47,567 --> 00:06:48,967
Aren't you happy?

115
00:06:49,333 --> 00:06:51,033
Your boyfriend is already
a vice mayor.

116
00:06:51,167 --> 00:06:52,600
We should be celebrating
tonight.

117
00:06:55,567 --> 00:06:56,867
I'm sorry, Glen.

118
00:06:58,033 --> 00:06:59,333
I'm just tired from work.

119
00:07:05,400 --> 00:07:07,667
Does the policeman
who's been pestering you

120
00:07:07,933 --> 00:07:09,300
have anything to do with this?

121
00:07:11,200 --> 00:07:13,500
Because if he doesn't stop...

122
00:07:14,967 --> 00:07:16,200
I'll make him shut up.

123
00:07:23,967 --> 00:07:26,233
Glen, you know what?

124
00:07:26,733 --> 00:07:27,433
You're right.

125
00:07:28,200 --> 00:07:29,333
We should celebrate.

126
00:07:30,467 --> 00:07:36,100
Why don't we go to my place
and celebrate there?

127
00:07:41,833 --> 00:07:43,700
Okay, I like that.

128
00:07:45,833 --> 00:07:46,467
Waiter...

129
00:07:47,933 --> 00:07:49,900
No need, just leave some money.
Let's go?

130
00:07:50,033 --> 00:07:51,267
- What?
- Let's go!

131
00:08:11,933 --> 00:08:12,700
Hi, Sir.

132
00:08:12,833 --> 00:08:14,467
Did you like something?

133
00:08:14,933 --> 00:08:15,700
I already did.

134
00:08:17,167 --> 00:08:20,900
It's just that it seems like
she likes someone else.

135
00:08:23,800 --> 00:08:25,167
I won't eat anymore.

136
00:08:27,133 --> 00:08:29,833
It's hard to eat
with a broken heart.

137
00:08:32,533 --> 00:08:33,733
Thank you.

138
00:08:39,633 --> 00:08:43,000
You know, Grandmother,
there's a new party drug now.

139
00:08:44,933 --> 00:08:48,667
And the scary thing is,
it's accessible and cheap.

140
00:08:49,433 --> 00:08:52,467
So tell the residents
from our village.

141
00:08:52,600 --> 00:08:55,133
Announce it, so the young people
can be warned.

142
00:08:55,433 --> 00:08:57,533
Because the drug
is on a pimple patch,

143
00:08:57,667 --> 00:08:59,033
the one that covers pimples.

144
00:09:00,100 --> 00:09:01,000
Pimple?

145
00:09:01,133 --> 00:09:02,267
Pimple?

146
00:09:02,400 --> 00:09:03,300
Yes.

147
00:09:04,167 --> 00:09:05,700
Someone has already died.

148
00:09:05,833 --> 00:09:09,467
And then the victim's companion
will probably go to jail.

149
00:09:09,600 --> 00:09:11,767
Lives are getting ruined.

150
00:09:12,867 --> 00:09:15,867
Those criminals are not going
to stop.

151
00:09:16,333 --> 00:09:18,100
So it's not acceptable
that we won't do anything.

152
00:09:21,467 --> 00:09:22,733
By the way, Grandmother...

153
00:09:24,633 --> 00:09:26,633
Mayor Guerrero has an offer
for me.

154
00:09:27,167 --> 00:09:30,733
He wants us to lead
the special task force.

155
00:09:30,900 --> 00:09:32,633
We'll work with him directly.

156
00:09:33,433 --> 00:09:34,233
What?

157
00:09:34,700 --> 00:09:36,233
You'll work with the mayor?

158
00:09:36,667 --> 00:09:37,233
Yes.

159
00:09:37,700 --> 00:09:39,533
Don't get involved in that.

160
00:09:40,333 --> 00:09:41,167
Stop that!

161
00:09:42,067 --> 00:09:42,767
Grandmother...

162
00:09:43,433 --> 00:09:44,200
Grandmother,

163
00:09:44,633 --> 00:09:46,433
why are you reacting like that
toward Mayor Guerrero?

164
00:09:47,900 --> 00:09:50,267
I know that you haven't
liked him ever since.

165
00:09:50,400 --> 00:09:51,967
But, Grandmother,
the election is over.

166
00:09:52,100 --> 00:09:53,333
That's okay.

167
00:09:53,467 --> 00:09:56,600
This isn't about who I support.

168
00:09:56,733 --> 00:09:58,767
All I'm saying is,
stay away from him.

169
00:09:58,900 --> 00:10:00,233
Don't get involved in that.

170
00:10:00,367 --> 00:10:03,433
But why are you reacting so
strongly against Mayor Joaquin?

171
00:10:04,233 --> 00:10:07,700
He's giving me the chance to
clean up the whole of Calabari.

172
00:10:07,833 --> 00:10:08,733
Why?

173
00:10:08,867 --> 00:10:11,733
You can do that too,
even if you don't join.

174
00:10:12,033 --> 00:10:15,200
Barbara Enriquez, don't join
that special task force.

175
00:10:15,967 --> 00:10:17,167
Grandmother, I'm sorry,

176
00:10:17,833 --> 00:10:20,000
but as long as you don't tell me
the real reason

177
00:10:20,133 --> 00:10:22,900
why you're doing this and why
you don't want me to join.

178
00:10:23,667 --> 00:10:26,967
I'm sorry, I can't follow you.

179
00:10:27,967 --> 00:10:30,333
I'll still join the mayor's
special task force.

180
00:10:38,100 --> 00:10:39,700
Miss, please cook
the seafood aglio olio.

181
00:10:39,833 --> 00:10:40,900
Add more shrimp.

182
00:10:41,033 --> 00:10:42,200
No matter how much,
name your price.

183
00:10:42,333 --> 00:10:43,400
- I'll take care of it.
- Yes.

184
00:10:43,533 --> 00:10:44,467
Does the chicken
taste like chicken?

185
00:10:44,600 --> 00:10:45,600
Check it out.

186
00:10:45,733 --> 00:10:48,533
Oh, come on. We prefer the ones
that are grilled...

187
00:10:48,667 --> 00:10:50,267
You should have knocked earlier,
so I would have known.

188
00:10:50,400 --> 00:10:53,467
That's what we ordered.
Just do it, Miss.

189
00:10:53,600 --> 00:10:54,767
I'm willing to pay
no matter how much.

190
00:10:54,900 --> 00:10:55,833
Knock early.

191
00:10:55,967 --> 00:10:56,967
Hey, Vince!

192
00:10:57,900 --> 00:10:59,467
You're a man, and you're getting
giddy over that?

193
00:10:59,600 --> 00:11:01,633
You even have hearts
in your message.

194
00:11:01,767 --> 00:11:03,700
I like the part that says,
"Congrats, Daddy."

195
00:11:03,833 --> 00:11:05,867
He even said "Daddy."

196
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:06,733
Daddy.

197
00:11:06,867 --> 00:11:08,567
You talk too much.

198
00:11:08,733 --> 00:11:10,067
- You know, Vince...
- Stop it!

199
00:11:10,333 --> 00:11:11,800
we're going to teach you
how to approach women.

200
00:11:11,933 --> 00:11:13,800
- Teach him, Bro.
- Use the right language.

201
00:11:13,933 --> 00:11:16,667
Say, "Faye, do you want
some wild mangosteen?"

202
00:11:17,633 --> 00:11:19,100
Why? What kind of wild
mangosteen is that?

203
00:11:19,233 --> 00:11:20,333
Someone like me.

204
00:11:22,067 --> 00:11:23,167
It's Boss Tonyo, Bro!

205
00:11:23,300 --> 00:11:25,033
- Boss Tonyo!
- Boss Tonyo!

206
00:11:25,167 --> 00:11:27,900
- Boss! Boss Tonyo!
- Let's drink! Let's go!

207
00:11:28,033 --> 00:11:29,533
It's too early for drinks.

208
00:11:31,000 --> 00:11:32,000
Is there even a right time
to drink, Boss?

209
00:11:32,133 --> 00:11:33,167
Before, as early
as four o'clock,

210
00:11:33,300 --> 00:11:34,767
you were already inviting us
for a drink.

211
00:11:35,133 --> 00:11:36,767
That was before, not anymore.

212
00:11:37,933 --> 00:11:39,800
- Boss has already changed.
- Well, Boss...

213
00:11:40,200 --> 00:11:41,900
What brings you here?
What happened?

214
00:11:42,067 --> 00:11:43,200
What's up, Boss?

215
00:11:43,500 --> 00:11:46,433
- We discovered a new drug.
- Drugs?

216
00:11:46,567 --> 00:11:47,900
It's a drug that's spreading
among young people

217
00:11:48,033 --> 00:11:49,100
in universities.

218
00:11:50,367 --> 00:11:51,800
I think I've heard about that,
Boss.

219
00:11:52,067 --> 00:11:54,633
Is that the one for pimples?

220
00:11:55,000 --> 00:11:56,667
Yes, that's it. You're right.

221
00:11:57,200 --> 00:12:00,033
So if you hear any information
about it,

222
00:12:00,733 --> 00:12:01,867
let me know right away, okay?

223
00:12:02,000 --> 00:12:02,800
Is that clear?

224
00:12:02,933 --> 00:12:04,033
Clear, Boss.

225
00:12:04,167 --> 00:12:06,967
But the thing is, Boss, it seems
like we're getting stupid

226
00:12:07,100 --> 00:12:08,133
when we're hungry.

227
00:12:08,267 --> 00:12:09,500
It's difficult to make a step
when you're hungry.

228
00:12:09,633 --> 00:12:11,067
It's painful here...

229
00:12:11,200 --> 00:12:12,800
- and my eyes are blurry.
- I'm getting weak.

230
00:12:14,467 --> 00:12:15,467
I can't breathe, Boss.

231
00:12:15,600 --> 00:12:17,833
What do you want?
Go ahead and get it.

232
00:12:17,967 --> 00:12:19,067
- Yes!
- Her niece...

233
00:12:19,200 --> 00:12:20,700
- You both scored again.
- The food that we ordered...

234
00:12:20,833 --> 00:12:22,867
That's enough, Boss.
There you go.

235
00:12:23,000 --> 00:12:24,500
Next time,

236
00:12:25,100 --> 00:12:27,233
- bring me breakfast, okay?
- No problem, Boss!

237
00:12:27,367 --> 00:12:28,033
No problem, Boss.

238
00:12:28,167 --> 00:12:29,533
You're not treating me.

239
00:12:29,667 --> 00:12:30,533
No, we'll take care of it.

240
00:12:30,667 --> 00:12:31,567
We'll bring you breakfast, Boss.

241
00:12:31,700 --> 00:12:33,567
Hey! Remember what I told you,
okay?

242
00:12:33,700 --> 00:12:34,533
Copy, Boss. Take care!

243
00:12:34,667 --> 00:12:36,133
Here's our payment
for the pasta.

244
00:12:36,267 --> 00:12:38,300
Seafood aglio olio,
additional shrimp.

245
00:12:38,433 --> 00:12:39,567
This is for my debt yesterday.

246
00:12:39,700 --> 00:12:41,867
Abdul, Bobby already said it,

247
00:12:42,000 --> 00:12:45,067
stop putting those patches
on your face.

248
00:12:45,333 --> 00:12:47,567
You know, you're overacting,
Mar.

249
00:12:47,867 --> 00:12:51,067
Bobby already mentioned
the pimple patches.

250
00:12:51,200 --> 00:12:52,633
It's useless, it doesn't have
any effect!

251
00:12:52,767 --> 00:12:53,367
Oh my...

252
00:12:55,700 --> 00:12:56,467
Bobby!

253
00:12:58,300 --> 00:13:00,233
- Why are you eating here?
- Yes.

254
00:13:00,533 --> 00:13:03,733
Captain Isang even cooked
your favorite breakfast.

255
00:13:03,867 --> 00:13:04,833
Yes, it's delicious.

256
00:13:04,967 --> 00:13:07,133
- I'm so full, I ate a lot.
- Same!

257
00:13:08,333 --> 00:13:09,833
I wasn't hungry earlier.

258
